tourBios.carHigh:
2015: Had a shot at the Dominican Republic Open title in June, an event he finished T4 for his best career finish in 19 career starts on PGA TOUR Latinoamérica. Moved into a tie for the lead with four holes to play, but dropped off contention with a bogey on 15 and a quadruple-bogey on 16… A week later, finished T24 at the Rust-Oleum Championship in his first start of the year on the Web.com Tour… Became the first player with two holes-in-one in a season on PGA TOUR Latinoamérica… His first was to win a car (a Chevrolet Matiz) during the third round of the 57th Abierto Mexicano de Golf, an event he T42 on PGA TOUR Latinoamérica in May. Hit a 9-iron from 147 yards (played closer to 130 yards factoring the elevation) for his ace at the par-3 No. 10 at Aguascalientes CC in Aguascalientes, Mexico… Six months later he had another hole-in-one during the second round of the Lexus Peru Open on his was to a T33 finish. Hit a 4-iron from 198 yards into the wind on No. 17, an uphill par-3… By season's end, had played nine Web.com Tour events and made seven cuts, with a T24 at the Digital Ally Open in August his best finish, along with his Rust-Oleum performance.

2014: Made the cut in 9 of his 19 starts on the Web.com Tour. Had two top-25s at the Utah Championship (T15) and the Air Capital Classic (T17). Finished the season ranked No. 123 on the money list… Made the cut in his four starts on PGA TOUR Latinoamérica, with a T12 at the Mazatlán Open as his best finish.

2013: Played nine events on PGA TOUR Latinoamérica, making six cuts. Had one top-10, a T8 at the Arturo Calle Colombian Classic after opening with a pair of 66s. Finished the season with five top-25s and was 38th on the Order of Merit. Joined PGA TOUR Latinoamérica by finishing T11 at the Q-School played in Sebring, Fla. in January... Finished third at Second Stage qualifier in Brooksville, Fla. to secure his spot in the Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament Finals. Shot 67-66 in the last two rounds at Finals to finish among the all-important top 45 and ties (T42).

2012: Played one event on the Web.com Tour, finishing T59 at the Cox Classic...Shot 64 in the second round. 

2011: Played one event on the Web.com Tour, missing the cut at the Nationwide Children's Hospital Championship.Carded a final round 65 to win his first professional event on the NGA Pro Golf Tour Winter Series at Orange County National in December.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Played college golf at the University of Iowa, where he earned medalist honors at the Baylor Intercollegiate, the Golfweek Conference Challenge and the Hawkeye-TaylorMade Invitational (T1) during his senior season, 2010-11… Was named 2011 Big Ten Player of the Year... 2011 University of Iowa Male Athlete of the Year... 2011 Second Team All-American… Also won the Les Bolstad Trophy for lowest season stroke average in the Big Ten. His 71.08 average is the lowest in Iowa U. history.... Named 2010 Cleveland Golf/Srixon All-America Scholar... Was a four-year golf team MVP at Deerfield High School... Four-time All-Conference honoree... Owns or shares every school individual golf record... Recorded three top-5 finishes on AJGA events between 2006-07.
tourBios.personal: Has one sister… Attended University of Iowa, where he earned a degree in Marketing in 2011… Attended Deerfield (Illionis) High School… Favorite course played is Inverness GC in Toledo, Ohio… Favorite teams are the Iowa Hawkeyes and Chicago Blackhawks, Chicago Bears and Chicago Bulls… Favorite TV shows are "Breaking Bad" and "Homeland."… Favorite movies are "Avatar" and "The Shawshank Redemption."… Likes the Harry Potter series of books… Favorite cities are Lima, Peru, and Montevideo, Uruguay… Dream pairing would include Paul Azinger and Alex Moen… First-tee introduction song would be "Rawhide."… Twitter: @vindia36… Instagram: @vindia2
